1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,700
To me, the Sixers are a five seat tops.

2
00:00:03,700 --> 00:00:05,540
I think they're going to the conference finals.

3
00:00:05,540 --> 00:00:06,340
No.

4
00:00:06,340 --> 00:00:07,340
Bynum.

5
00:00:07,340 --> 00:00:08,340
Obvious monster.

6
00:00:08,340 --> 00:00:09,340
I have three point shooting.

7
00:00:09,340 --> 00:00:11,180
Don't you...

8
00:00:11,180 --> 00:00:14,420
I bit my lip at lunch today.

9
00:00:14,420 --> 00:00:15,920
Sucks.

10
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:17,220
Anyway, I just don't see it.

11
00:00:17,220 --> 00:00:18,880
The nicks are tough.

12
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:19,960
The nets are tough.

13
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:21,880
Oh, the nets are super tough.

14
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:26,100
Now I have this big bump in my lip that hurts.

15
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,920
I hate it.

16
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:30,620
The hooks are terrible.

17
00:00:30,620 --> 00:00:32,160
They're always terrible.

18
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:35,760
Okay, you need to think about it before you come with the...

19
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:38,760
...

20
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:40,060
Whatever.

21
00:00:40,060 --> 00:00:41,060
It's not a big deal.

22
00:00:41,060 --> 00:00:42,300
You know, I always tell my three year old,

23
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:44,440
if this is the worst thing that's going to happen,

24
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:45,860
you got to be kidding me.

25
00:00:45,860 --> 00:00:46,940
Okay.

26
00:00:46,940 --> 00:00:48,900
Pam, that's it.

27
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:49,900
I'm going home.

28
00:00:52,540 --> 00:00:55,080
Maybe that's a shopping list.

29
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:58,040
He's buying a ham, skeleton, and a rainbow?

30
00:00:58,040 --> 00:01:00,440
It's Creed.

31
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:03,280
We found this weird drawing under Creed's desk.

32
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,980
So bizarre.

33
00:01:07,260 --> 00:01:09,260
Oh my God.

34
00:01:09,260 --> 00:01:10,460
It's a map.

35
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:11,320
Of course.

36
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:13,660
Okay, so the waves, water.

37
00:01:13,660 --> 00:01:14,760
The water cooler.

38
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:17,120
And a hammes, food, the kitchen.

39
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,400
The bucket is the bathroom.

40
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,600
It's a map of the office.

41
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,100
Bingo.

42
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:22,460
Who's the skeleton?

43
00:01:22,460 --> 00:01:24,840
Angela.

44
00:01:24,860 --> 00:01:26,200
You're the cheeseburger.

45
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,000
Hey.

46
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,700
What am I?

47
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:30,300
I don't know.

48
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:31,800
The toilet.

49
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,800
He used the bucket to signify the bathroom,

50
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:36,140
the toilet to signify me.

51
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:38,140
I'm sorry.

52
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:45,880
Hello.

53
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:46,980
Hey Creed.

54
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:49,160
Are you lost?

55
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:49,760
What?

56
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:50,660
No.

57
00:01:50,660 --> 00:01:52,660
Lost in the office?

58
00:01:52,660 --> 00:01:54,660
Nope.

59
00:01:54,860 --> 00:01:56,700
Anybody going back to the little pinch soon?

60
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:57,600
I am.

61
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:58,800
Want some company?

62
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,800
Okay.

63
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,980
Morning Meredith.

64
00:02:17,980 --> 00:02:19,220
What?

65
00:02:19,220 --> 00:02:20,020
Oh, sorry.

66
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:21,220
Pam.

67
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:23,560
Yikes.

68
00:02:23,580 --> 00:02:26,220
Jim's been spending a few days a week in Philly,

69
00:02:26,220 --> 00:02:30,120
and I'm not going to lie, it's been challenging.

70
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:34,160
Yesterday things took a turn for the worse.

71
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:36,360
I found out Cece has lice.

72
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:40,400
So I was up all night disinfecting every sheet,

73
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:44,700
towel, toy, item of clothing in the entire house.

74
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,900
I'm exhausted.

75
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,540
But don't tell Jim.

76
00:02:48,540 --> 00:02:52,900
He has a huge meeting today, under a lot of pressure.

77
00:02:52,980 --> 00:02:56,860
And he's doing it all for the family.

78
00:02:56,860 --> 00:02:58,120
Hey.

79
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,620
There he is.

80
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:00,660
You cool for today?

81
00:03:00,660 --> 00:03:02,260
Cool?

82
00:03:02,260 --> 00:03:05,560
Curse if I'm so cool, I'm frozen.

83
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,160
Sorry.

84
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:08,200
I will not talk like that.

85
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:10,960
I'll be cool.

86
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:14,000
I am meeting Dr. J today, otherwise known

87
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,280
as Julius Irving, Fame 76er, and my own personal hero.

88
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,440
But I have to be careful not to rub in Pam's face,

89
00:03:20,460 --> 00:03:22,860
because let's be honest, how would I

90
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:24,900
feel if I was at home stuck with the kids

91
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:29,300
while she was go-karting with John Stamos?

92
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:30,360
You sound tired.

93
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,460
Everything OK?

94
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:32,060
Great.

95
00:03:32,060 --> 00:03:33,340
Everything's great.

96
00:03:33,340 --> 00:03:35,980
Hey, are you nervous about your big meeting?

97
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:36,780
A little bit.

98
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:38,860
It's a lot of pressure, you know.

99
00:03:38,860 --> 00:03:40,620
But that's what I signed up for, right?

100
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:43,780
Jim, Flimmel's here.

101
00:03:43,780 --> 00:03:47,300
You know what, I got to hop off because my taxi is here

102
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:48,700
to take me to the meeting.

103
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:49,740
Oh, call me later.

104
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:50,240
OK.

105
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:50,740
Talk.

106
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:51,240
Thanks.

107
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:51,740
I love you.

108
00:03:51,740 --> 00:03:52,340
Love you, too.

109
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:52,840
Bye.

110
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,420
How you doing?

111
00:03:56,420 --> 00:03:57,180
OK.

112
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:58,700
I mean, it's what you want, so.

113
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,340
It's how it has to be.

114
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:00,840
I know.

115
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,380
I know.

116
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:03,540
It's just hard.

117
00:04:03,540 --> 00:04:05,860
Me and Val were going nowhere.

118
00:04:05,860 --> 00:04:07,580
And if I'm going to be working in Philly,

119
00:04:07,580 --> 00:04:09,100
I'm going to need my freedom.

120
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:11,460
So I convinced Val to break out with me.

121
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:12,500
Here's how you do it.

122
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:15,340
You say, what are you going to do, break out with me?

123
00:04:15,340 --> 00:04:16,620
Like, as a joke.

124
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:18,780
And then you gain a lot of weight.

125
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,160
I'll never be sorry, not for a moment of it.

126
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:21,660
Me neither.

127
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,280
Hey, Meredith.

128
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,840
I need your supply requests today.

129
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,000
She was eight in the morning.

130
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,760
Will you stop your nagging already?

131
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,080
No wonder Jim left you.

132
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:33,880
He didn't leave me.

133
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:35,200
He just went part time.

134
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,840
Can you just fill out the form, please?

135
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:41,340
Yes.

136
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,200
I'm sure she's just confused.

137
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:49,980
People scratch their heads when they're confused.

138
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:52,380
Not always like an ape, the way Meredith just did.

139
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:53,940
But it happens.
